##### README #####
In order to run this automation pack, you will need to do the following:

1) Install Python 2.7
   Download from https://www.python.org/downloads/

2) Install Lettuce
   Once Python has been installed, using Command Prompt (PC) / Terminal (Mac), navigate to your Python directory
   e.g. 'cd /Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7'

   Run the following command:
   For PC: 'pip install lettuce'
   For Mac: 'sudo pip install lettuce'

   -- Note --
   If you receive any errors relating to 'pip', you may have to install pip by doing the following:
   Download get-pip.py from https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py
   Place the file inside your Python directory e.g. /Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7/
   Run the command 'python get-pip.py'

3) Install Selenium
   Navigate to your Python directory in Command Prompt / Terminal (see task 2)
   Run the following command:
   For PC: 'pip install selenium'
   For Mac: 'sudo pip install selenium'

4) Run a feature file
   In order to run a feature file, navigate to your Python directory in Command Prompt / Terminal (see task 2)
   Run the command 'lettuce [insert path to feature file]'
   e.g. for a particular feature file
   'lettuce /Users/ammarahahmad/PycharmProjects/asos/features/taskone.feature'

   Run the following in the file path:

   lettuce taskone.feature
   lettuce tasktwo.feature
   lettuce taskthree.feature
   lettuce taskfour.feature